For EACH relationship type, the required output structure is shown below.
Return only NEW relationships not already in the KG.

{% for r in relationship_ontology_rich %}
{{ r.type }}:
  {
    "type": "{{ r.type }}",
    "source": "<id of a {{ r.from | join(' or ') }} entity>",
    "target": "<id of a {{ r.to | join(' or ') }} entity>",
    "attributes": {
      "evidence": "<verbatim or paraphrased quote — REQUIRED>",
{% if r.attributes is mapping and r.attributes %}{% for attr, atype in r.attributes.items() %}      "{{ attr }}": "<{{ atype }} or null>",
{% endfor %}{% endif %}    }
  }
{% endfor %}

Return:
{
  "relationships": [ ... one object per relationship found, using the exact structure above ... ],
  "relationships_to_remove": []
}

Rules:
- Use ONLY ontology-defined relationship types.
- source/target must match the allowed From/To entity types.
- Include ONLY the attribute keys shown for this relationship type plus "evidence". Do NOT add any other keys.
- Fill each attribute with a value matching its specified type. Use null only if the value is genuinely not present.
- "evidence" is REQUIRED and must never be null or empty.
- Do NOT include a "reasoning" field.
- Only include NEW relationships. Do NOT repeat existing correct ones.
